1\. Purpose

The purpose of the app is to provide users with a virtual pet experience where they can virtually experience how it is to take care of a pet. In this app they can feed the virtual dog, wash it and play with it, this way users get to experience real life activities of having a dog but virtually on their phones or laptops. The app can be used for both educational and entertainment purposes. The educational purpose of the app is for users to learn and gain experience on how to tackle a responsibility of taking acre of something else besides themselves. Users will learn the responsibility of how it is important to care for other living things. The users can also learn how to prioritise and manage their time to ensure that the pet remains well taken care of properly and this way they also learn the skill on time management. The entertainment purpose of the app would be having fun playing with the virtual pet and interacting with it as you do so.

**General design**

The design of the app is suitable and safe for children to play with. It is appropriate, colourful and the pictures are visually appealing to children. The name if the app is catchy and easy to remember. The design of the app is visually appealing because of the high quality images used that enhances the user experience in the app. The features of the app are easy to navigate and to use, as they are also easily accessible. The design is not just appealing to children but it can also be for older children and adults. The font and design remain consistent throughout the app and the images are not too big nor too small to see. The design accommodates all users and especially ones with disabilities. It is very accessible to everyone, everywhere and anytime. The theme of the app aligns with the type of app it is to help users create visual image in their heads when they use the app, which also helps to enhance user engagement via a more enjoyable and fulfilling experience.

**Intuitive design**

The design of the app is easy to navigate so users do not have any difficulties while using the app. It is a simple design structure that has the proper labelling that are straightforward and clear to understand. Users will be able to find what they are looking for when they are trying to use specific features while using the app. The design is ensured to live up to the users expectations and imaginary. Every feature is situated in a way that it is neat and is where it can be expected to be found within the app. There is proper coordination with the pictures, buttons and other features.

**Content prioritisation**

The essential elements that are displayed for content and functionalities for the user’s needs are the buttons, high quality images, labels and text fields. All the interface elements that are within the app are all necessary for the app to actually run and to meet the user’s needs and wants. The interface elements also contribute the functionality of the app so the contents can display on the app. The labels in the app are primarily used to provide the users with descriptive text that state the other interface elements purpose so they can be able to tell which does what task that they desire to see.

**Legible Text Content**

All the text in the app are visibly clear and the size large enough and bold to see and to be read. The content is legible for users to comprehend without any complications. There is suitable indentation throughout the app. This way users with eye problems do not have any problems trying to navigate the app, so everyone is well accommodated to their needs.

**Make Interface Elements Clearly Visible**

The components on the screen are clear and visible to see. The spacing of the text, images and the buttons are appropriately spaced suitably, consistently and there is no cluster. The content is not too close or too far away from one another, consistently so throughout the whole app.

**Hand Position Controls**

The positions of each button are well designed so users can easily locate them. The buttons perform their action tasks within the app when they are put to use. The controls of the buttons

**Images**

The images of the pets are of high quality and appealing to anyone who loves pets. The images go with the theme of the design of the app and they also make the app more appealing which will increase the user’s interest in the app. They images are used to grab the attention of users into wanting to have and use the app.

**Code from both activities (the main activity and the game activity):**

class MainActivity : AppCompatActivity() {

override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {

super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)

setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)

// Button to navigate to the second screen

val startButton = findViewById &lt;Button&gt; (R.id.startButton)

startButton.setOnClickListener {

val intent = Intent (this, GameActivity::class.java)

// GameActivity: name of the second activity

// Pass the message "I am hungry" as an extra with the intent

intent.putExtra("FEED_MESSAGE", "I am hungry")

//This will be shown in the feedTextView

startActivity(intent)

}

}

}

class GameActivity : AppCompatActivity() {

@SuppressLint("MissingInflatedId")

override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {

setContentView(R.layout.activity_game)

// Retrieve the message passed from the first screen
